pageTitle: You can prevent bloat in calves | Hoards Dairyman
TableContextTimeStampBeforeTable: {10024=It also is important to establish a consistent feeding schedule. If you’re feeding twice a day, it doesn’t have to be at exactly 12-hour intervals. You may choose to feed at 8 in the morning and then again at 4:30 in the afternoon. However, it is important to be consistent. Feeding calves “sometime during the morning” and then again “sometime during the evening” will add to your risk of bloat. If you have a bloated calf, it is important to call your veterinarian. These calves often will die fairly quickly, so rapid evaluation and treatment is important.}
